@startuml
actor Student
actor Lecturer
actor Admin
participant Browser
participant "SubmissionController" as Controller
participant "SubmissionService" as SubmissionService
participant "AssignmentService" as AssignmentService
participant "ICryptoService" as Crypto
participant "SubmissionContentEncryptionService" as Encrypt
participant "SubmissionKeyProtectionService" as KeyProtect
participant "FileSystemSubmissionContentStore" as Store
participant "AuditService" as Audit
database DB

Browser -> Controller : GET /api/auth/csrf over HTTPS
Controller --> Browser : readable XSRF-TOKEN cookie

Student -> Browser : choose assignment visible through current space membership
Browser -> Controller : POST /api/assignments/{assignmentId}/submissions\nmultipart/form-data + credentialed auth cookie + X-XSRF-TOKEN
Controller -> SubmissionService : createSubmission(currentUser, assignmentId, file)
SubmissionService -> AssignmentService : getStudentAccessibleAssignmentOrThrow(currentUser, assignmentId)
AssignmentService -> DB : load assignment + student space visibility
DB --> AssignmentService : assignment + current visibility
AssignmentService --> SubmissionService : visible assignment
SubmissionService -> SubmissionService : validate file presence, size, type,\nPDF header / UTF-8 constraints, and open assignment state
SubmissionService -> Crypto : hash(plaintext bytes) using SHA-256
Crypto --> SubmissionService : hashDigest
SubmissionService -> Crypto : sign(hashDigest bytes)
Crypto --> SubmissionService : digitalSignature
SubmissionService -> Crypto : verify(hashDigest bytes, digitalSignature)
Crypto --> SubmissionService : verification result
SubmissionService -> Encrypt : encrypt(plaintext) with fresh AES-GCM nonce + DEK
Encrypt --> SubmissionService : ciphertext + nonce + content-encryption key
SubmissionService -> KeyProtect : wrap(content-encryption key)
KeyProtect --> SubmissionService : wrapped key + key version
SubmissionService -> Store : store(ciphertext)
Store --> SubmissionService : storedFileReference
SubmissionService -> DB : persist submission metadata, digest, signature,\nverification state, and encryption metadata
SubmissionService -> Audit : record SUBMISSION_CREATED
SubmissionService -> Audit : record SUBMISSION_VERIFIED or SUBMISSION_VERIFICATION_FAILED
SubmissionService --> Controller : SubmissionResponse (metadata only)
Controller --> Browser : 201 Created + metadata-only JSON

Lecturer -> Controller : GET /api/submissions/{submissionId}\ncredentialed auth cookie request
Controller -> SubmissionService : getSubmission(submissionId, actor)
SubmissionService -> DB : load submission metadata + verification state
DB --> SubmissionService : metadata + verification state + grade linkage
SubmissionService --> Controller : SubmissionResponse
Controller --> Lecturer : digest, signature, verificationStatus, message

Admin -> Controller : GET /api/submissions/{submissionId}\ncredentialed auth cookie request
Controller -> SubmissionService : getSubmission(submissionId, actor)
SubmissionService --> Controller : SubmissionResponse
Controller --> Admin : metadata with global oversight access

Student -> Controller : GET /api/submissions/{submissionId}/content\ncredentialed auth cookie request
Controller -> SubmissionService : getSubmissionContent(submissionId, actor)
SubmissionService -> DB : load submission + authorise student ownership\nor lecturer/admin assignment access
DB --> SubmissionService : accessible submission + storage metadata
SubmissionService -> Store : read(ciphertext by storedFileReference)
Store --> SubmissionService : ciphertext
SubmissionService -> KeyProtect : unwrap(content-encryption key)
KeyProtect --> SubmissionService : plaintext DEK
SubmissionService -> Encrypt : decrypt(ciphertext, nonce, DEK)
Encrypt --> SubmissionService : plaintext content
SubmissionService -> Audit : record SUBMISSION_CONTENT_ACCESSED
SubmissionService --> Controller : SubmissionContentResponse
Controller --> Student : decrypted file bytes

note right of SubmissionService
 The implemented flow now:
 - validates assignment visibility and open state
 - validates upload size and supported file types
 - computes SHA-256 digest
 - signs and verifies the digest immediately
 - encrypts stored content with AES-GCM
 - wraps the DEK before persistence

 Student submission and student self-service retrieval
 depend on the related assignment remaining visible
 through current space membership.
 Lecturer access is owner-scoped by assignment,
 while admins retain global oversight.
end note

note right of Store
 Standard metadata responses do not expose ciphertext,
 wrapped keys, nonce values, or storedFileReference.
 Plaintext retrieval is a separate authorised path via
 GET /api/submissions/{submissionId}/content.
end note
@enduml

